message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The location of the mass above the sella turcica suggests that it is a craniopharyngioma, which is derived from remnants of the oral ectoderm. The neuroectoderm gives rise to the neural tissue and structures such as the brain and spinal cord. The neurohypophysis is the posterior lobe of the pituitary gland, and paraxial mesoderm gives rise to the musculoskeletal system. None of these are related to the location or characteristics of the described mass.
